You could simply use a `private` backing field using [`[SerializeField]`](https://docs.unity3d.com/ScriptReference/SerializeField.html) instead

    [XmlElement(&quot;WebWellConfiguration&quot;)] 
    // [SerializeField] allows to mark private fields for serialization
    [SerializeField] private WebWellConfiguration wellConfig;
    
    // since this is now no longer an auto-property but
    // using a backing field this one won&#39;t be serialized at all
    public WebWellConfiguration WellConfig 
    { 
        get { return wellConfig; } 
        protected set { wellConfig = value; }
    }

One more bonus side-effect of doing this: You now also should be able to see and configure this field via the Unity Inspector!
    
---

*Assuming of course `WebWellConfiguration` is `[Serializable]` already anyway .. otherwise it wouldn&#39;t be able to be (de)serialized at all.*

